OL,7,FHe said it was intended to clarify
OL,8,Fthat the Alabama Constitution does not
OL,9,Fprotect the right to abortion and
OL,10,Feventually laid the groundwork for
OL,11,FAlabama to ban abortions when states
OL,12,Fregained control of abortion access.
OL,14,FHowever, opponents of the
OL,15,Fconstitutional amendment warned in
OL,16,F2018 that it was essentially a
OL,17,Fpersonhood measure that could give
OL,18,Frights to fertilised eggs.
